# Refactoring Summary: Step Definitions to Pure Page Object Model

## 📋 Changes Made

### ✅ What Was Fixed

#### **Before (Anti-Pattern ❌)**
Step definitions contained direct UI interaction code:
```csharp
[When(@"I click on ""(.*)"" button")]
public void WhenIClickOnButton(string buttonName)
{
    // ❌ UI locator logic in step definition
    var button = _paintMainPage!.MainWindow.FindFirstDescendant(cf => 
        cf.ByName(buttonName).And(cf.ByControlType(ControlType.Button)));
    
    if (button != null)
    {
        button.Click();
        Thread.Sleep(300);
    }
}

[When(@"I draw a line from (.*),(.*) to (.*),(.*)")]
public void WhenIDrawALineFrom(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2)
{
    // ❌ Direct FlaUI calls in step definition
    var canvas = _paintMainPage!.MainWindow.FindFirstDescendant(cf => 
        cf.ByControlType(ControlType.Pane));
    
    var bounds = canvas.BoundingRectangle;
    Mouse.MoveTo(startX, startY);
    Mouse.Down(MouseButton.Left);
    // ... more FlaUI code
}
```

#### **After (Correct Pattern ✅)**
Step definitions only orchestrate and assert:
```csharp
[When(@"I click on ""(.*)"" button")]
public void WhenIClickOnButton(string buttonName)
{
    _paintMainPage!.ClickButton(buttonName);  // ✅ Delegates to Page Object
}

[When(@"I draw a line from (.*),(.*) to (.*),(.*)")]
public void WhenIDrawALineFrom(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2)
{
    _paintMainPage!.DrawLine(x1, y1, x2, y2);  // ✅ Delegates to Page Object
}

[Then(@"the Paint canvas should be visible")]
public void ThenThePaintCanvasShouldBeVisible()
{
    Assert.That(_paintMainPage!.IsCanvasVisible(), Is.True);  // ✅ Assertion only
}
```

