## ✅ Code Review Checklist

Use this checklist when reviewing or writing new code:

### Step Definitions (*.Steps.cs)
- [ ] No `FindFirstDescendant` calls
- [ ] No `ByName`, `ByControlType`, etc.
- [ ] No `Mouse`, `Keyboard` direct calls
- [ ] Only Page Object method calls
- [ ] Assertions only in `Then` steps
- [ ] Clear, descriptive method names
- [ ] Adequate wait times for dialogs (≥1000ms)
- [ ] Explicit `WaitForPageLoad()` calls

### Page Objects (*Page.cs)
- [ ] All UI locators encapsulated
- [ ] All FlaUI interactions encapsulated
- [ ] No assertions (Assert.That, etc.)
- [ ] No test orchestration logic
- [ ] Returns data for verification
- [ ] Throws meaningful exceptions
- [ ] Methods are atomic and focused
- [ ] Retry logic for timing-sensitive operations
- [ ] Check element state before interaction (`IsEnabled`, `IsReadOnly`)

## 📚 Training Example

### ❌ Bad Example (Don't Do This)
```csharp
// Step Definition
[When(@"I select ""(.*)"" color")]
public void WhenISelectColor(string color)
{
    var colorButton = _mainWindow.FindFirstDescendant(cf =>  // ❌ UI logic
        cf.ByName(color).And(cf.ByControlType(ControlType.Button)));
    colorButton?.Click();  // ❌ Direct interaction
}
```

### ✅ Good Example (Do This)
```csharp
// Step Definition
[When(@"I select ""(.*)"" color")]
public void WhenISelectColor(string color)
{
    _paintMainPage!.SelectColor(color);  // ✅ Delegates to Page Object
}

// Page Object
public void SelectColor(string colorName)
{
    var colorButton = MainWindow.FindFirstDescendant(cf =>  // ✅ Encapsulated
        cf.ByName(colorName).And(cf.ByControlType(ControlType.Button)));
    
    if (colorButton != null)
    {
        colorButton.Click();  // ✅ Encapsulated
        Thread.Sleep(200);
    }
    else
    {
        throw new ElementNotFoundException($"Color '{colorName}' not found");
    }
}
```

